Tammy Abraham opened the scoring for Chelsea with a fine strike with just seven minutes of the game played . 
 But, Chelsea's lead didn't last long as the hosts levelled the scores two minutes later via Isaac Buckley . 
 Some poor defending from Manchester City allowed Abraham to grab an acrobatic second to restore their lead . 
 Chelsea wrapped up the win in the closing stages when Dominic Solanke broke free and slotted an effort home . 
 